c \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} dx \, e^{-|x-1|} = 1
\begin{align}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} dx \, e^{-|x-1|} &= \int_{-\infty}^1 dx \, e^{(x-1)} + \int_1^{\infty} dx \, e^{-(x-1)}\\ &= 2 \int_0^{\infty} dx \, e^{-x}\\ &= 2\end{align}
c=1/2
